016  // reserved hive words
017  public static final Set<String> SQL_RESERVED_WORDS = Set.of("date", "order", "format", "group");

022  private static final Set<? extends Term> EXTENSION_TERMS =
023      Arrays.stream(Extension.values())
024          .map(ext -> TermFactory.instance().findTerm(ext.getRowType()))
025          .collect(Collectors.toSet());

093  private SQLColumnsUtils() {
094    // empty constructor
095  }
096
097  public static String getSQLColumn(Term term) {
098    if (GbifTerm.verbatimScientificName == term) {
099      return "v_" + DwcTerm.scientificName.simpleName().toLowerCase();
100    }
101    String columnName = term.simpleName().toLowerCase();
102    if (SQL_RESERVED_WORDS.contains(columnName)) {
103      return columnName + '_';
104    }
105    return columnName;
106  }
107
108  /** Gets the Hive column name of the term parameter. */
109  public static String getSQLQueryColumn(Term term) {
110    String columnName = getSQLColumn(term);
111    if (isHumboldtTerm(term)) {
112      columnName = "h." + columnName;
113    }
114    return isVocabulary(term) ? columnName + ".lineage" : columnName;
115  }
116
117  /** Gets the Hive column name of the term parameter. */
118  public static String getSQLValueColumn(Term term) {
119    String columnName = getSQLColumn(term);
120    return isVocabulary(term)
121        ? isSQLArray(term) ? columnName + ".concepts" : columnName + ".concept"
122        : columnName;
123  }
124
125  /** Gets the Hive column name of the extension parameter. */
126  public static String getSQLQueryColumn(Extension extension) {
127    return EXTENSION_PRE + extension.name().toLowerCase();
128  }
129
130  /** Returns the Hive data type of term parameter. */
131  public static String getSQLType(Term term) {
132    if (isInterpretedNumerical(term)) {
133      return "INT";
134    } else if (isInterpretedLocalDateSeconds(term)) {
135      return "BIGINT";
136    } else if (isInterpretedUtcDateSeconds(term)) {
137      return "BIGINT";
138    } else if (isInterpretedUtcDateMilliseconds(term)) {
139      return "BIGINT";
140    } else if (isInterpretedDouble(term)) {
141      return "DOUBLE";
142    } else if (isInterpretedBoolean(term)) {
143      return "BOOLEAN";
144    } else if (isVocabulary(term)) {
145      if (isSQLArray(term)) {
146        return "STRUCT<concepts: ARRAY<STRING>,lineage: ARRAY<STRING>>";
147      } else {
148        return "STRUCT<concept: STRING,lineage: ARRAY<STRING>>";
149      }
150    } else if (isSQLArray(term)) {
151      return "ARRAY<STRING>";
152    } else {
153      return "STRING";
154    }
155  }
156
157  public static boolean isDate(Term term) {
158    return isInterpretedLocalDateSeconds(term)
159        || isInterpretedUtcDateSeconds(term)
160        || isInterpretedUtcDateMilliseconds(term);
161  }
162
163  /** Checks if the term is stored as a Hive array. */
164  public static boolean isSQLArray(Term term) {
165    return GbifTerm.mediaType == term
166        || GbifTerm.issue == term
167        || GbifInternalTerm.networkKey == term
168        || DwcTerm.identifiedByID == term
169        || DwcTerm.recordedByID == term
170        || GbifInternalTerm.dwcaExtension == term
171        || DwcTerm.datasetID == term
172        || DwcTerm.datasetName == term
173        || DwcTerm.typeStatus == term
174        || DwcTerm.otherCatalogNumbers == term
175        || DwcTerm.recordedBy == term
176        || DwcTerm.identifiedBy == term
177        || DwcTerm.preparations == term
178        || DwcTerm.samplingProtocol == term
179        || DwcTerm.georeferencedBy == term
180        || DwcTerm.higherGeography == term
181        || GbifTerm.projectId == term
182        || GbifTerm.lithostratigraphy == term
183        || GbifTerm.biostratigraphy == term
184        || GbifTerm.nonTaxonomicIssue == term
185        || EcoTerm.voucherInstitutions == term
186        || EcoTerm.verbatimSiteNames == term
187        || EcoTerm.verbatimSiteDescriptions == term
188        || EcoTerm.compilationSourceTypes == term
189        || EcoTerm.targetHabitatScope == term
190        || EcoTerm.excludedHabitatScope == term
191        || EcoTerm.targetGrowthFormScope == term
192        || EcoTerm.excludedGrowthFormScope == term
193        || EcoTerm.taxonCompletenessProtocols == term
194        || EcoTerm.samplingPerformedBy == term
195        || EcoTerm.compilationTypes == term
196        || EcoTerm.materialSampleTypes == term
197        || EcoTerm.inventoryTypes == term
198        || EcoTerm.protocolNames == term
199        || EcoTerm.protocolDescriptions == term
200        || EcoTerm.protocolReferences == term
201        || EcoTerm.targetLifeStageScope == term
202        || EcoTerm.targetDegreeOfEstablishmentScope == term
203        || EcoTerm.excludedLifeStageScope == term
204        || EcoTerm.excludedDegreeOfEstablishmentScope == term
205        || DwcTerm.projectTitle == term
206        || DwcTerm.fundingAttribution == term
207        || DwcTerm.fundingAttributionID == term;
208  }
209
210  public static boolean isHumboldtTerm(Term term) {
211    return term instanceof EcoTerm || term == GbifInternalTerm.humboldtEventDurationValueInMinutes;
212  }
213
214  public static boolean isVocabulary(Term term) {
215    return term instanceof Enum && hasTermAnnotation(term, Vocabulary.class);
216  }
217
218  private static boolean hasTermAnnotation(Term term, Class<? extends Annotation> annotation) {
219    try {
220      return term.getClass().getField(((Enum) term).name()).isAnnotationPresent(annotation);
221    } catch (NoSuchFieldException var3) {
222      throw new IllegalArgumentException(var3);
223    }
224  }
225
226  /** @return true if the term is an interpreted local date (timezone not relevant) */
227  public static boolean isInterpretedLocalDateSeconds(Term term) {
228    return term != null && INTERPRETED_LOCAL_DATES_SECONDS.contains(term);
229  }
230
231  /** @return true if the term is an interpreted UTC date stored in seconds */
232  public static boolean isInterpretedUtcDateSeconds(Term term) {
233    return term != null && INTERPRETED_UTC_DATES_SECONDS.contains(term);
234  }
235
236  /** @return true if the term is an interpreted UTC date stored in milliseconds */
237  public static boolean isInterpretedUtcDateMilliseconds(Term term) {
238    return term != null && INTERPRETED_UTC_DATES_MILLISECONDS.contains(term);
239  }
240
241  /** @return true if the term is an interpreted numerical */
242  public static boolean isInterpretedNumerical(Term term) {
243    return term != null && INTERPRETED_NUM.contains(term);
244  }
245
246  /** @return true if the term is an interpreted double */
247  public static boolean isInterpretedDouble(Term term) {
248    return term != null && INTERPRETED_DOUBLE.contains(term);
249  }
250
251  /** @return true if the term is an interpreted boolean */
252  public static boolean isInterpretedBoolean(Term term) {
253    return term != null && INTERPRETED_BOOLEAN.contains(term);
254  }
255
256  /** @return true if the term is a complex type in Hive: array, struct, json, etc. */
257  public static boolean isComplexType(Term term) {
258    return term != null && COMPLEX_TYPE.contains(term);
259  }
260
261  public static boolean isExtensionTerm(Term term) {
262    return term != null && EXTENSION_TERMS.contains(term);
263  }
